abstract: QuinStreet, an Internet marketer that competes with Yahoo and Google, is the one beacon of hope in this week’s crop of initial public offerings as the market contends with jitters spurred by concerns about the economy.
snippet: QuinStreet, an Internet marketer that competes with Yahoo and Google, is the one beacon of hope in this week’s crop of initial public offerings as the market contends with jitters spurred by concerns about the economy.
lead_paragraph: QuinStreet, an Internet marketer, is the one beacon of hope in this week’s crop of initial public offerings as the market contends with jitters spurred by concerns about the economy, and I.P.O.’s from companies with more than their fair share of debt, The Associated Press writes.

headline.main: QuinStreet Called Beacon of Hope in ‘Lousy’ I.P.O. Market

abstract: Google’s Buzz service, which ties into Gmail, is another way for people to tell others what they’re doing, thinking and feeling.
snippet: Google’s Buzz service, which ties into Gmail, is another way for people to tell others what they’re doing, thinking and feeling.
lead_paragraph: Feeling overwhelmed by the bevy of social networking services? Google wants to help — by adding one to the list. On Tuesday the company unveiled Google Buzz, another way for people to tell other people what they’re doing, thinking and feeling.

headline.main: Google Gets More Social With Buzz

abstract: After mounting complaints about the lack of customer support for the Nexus One, Google is offering a phone hot line.
snippet: After mounting complaints about the lack of customer support for the Nexus One, Google is offering a phone hot line.
lead_paragraph: As my colleague Miguel Helft and I recently reported, new owners of the Nexus One, the touch-screen smartphone developed by Google, have found themselves at a loss when it comes to receiving customer support for the device.

headline.main: Google Offers Phone Help for Nexus One Owners

abstract: Federal prosecutors brought new charges against Raj Rajaratnam in the Galleon Group insider trading case on Tuesday, expanding the number of stocks that they say were traded based on inside information.
